channel.title: Something is RESETting my eUICC during a profile download - HL7800
channel.description:
I'm running a mangOH Red with an HL7800 module. I'm attempting to download a new profile to an eUICC and something, possibly the the mangOH firmware, is resetting the SIM during the download. I get this from simtrace2:
``` TPDU (incomplete): 80 14 00 00 ff 81 03 01 42 00 82 02 82 81 83 01 00 b6 81 ed 42 72 5c ad 99 d3 79 3c 57 24 02 b8 b6 90 1e 4c a6 f8 e4 7c 92 6d 1b 39 24 f8 10 c0 84 ff 3f b7 08 db 6a 10 4d 65 08 43 a2 87 46 ed f5 47 86 c3 2d af ad 17 0c 83 81 b6 23 e7 98 8d 28 fd 50 c0 60 20 15 07 1c bc 53 c3 6f b7 a5 33 3d 99 e9 dd 64 a9 13 fc 38 63 88 e5 94 84 18 5f 3b 1a f0 cc e5 f0 70 b4 96 54 20 a4 96 95 d6 2b 8e 6b 11 4a 83 dd 8a 0d 3c 3f ae 51 62 ad 43 6d 79 e4 76 d6 ee 6f 45 20 83 30 5f 8b e9 5d d3 e2 de d3 da 4c 61 a9 e9 0c 57 1e 22 65 57 63 38 94 94 2f 30 c2 f9 0c e0 c9 fc f3 03 1d b1 05 86 87 4f 9f 33 b0 cb df e4 6f d3 52 54 f9 e9 3c 03 4c 97 a2 39 4e ef 6c f1 28 34 a0 42 82 6e bd 2d 31 aa 41 5f 5d bd 49 37 ac a5 9c bb 64 82 ab ea c8 fb e9 62 cb fb 72 7e a3 2f 77 63 72 a4 9a 04 6d 8a 37 01 ff Card state change: reset asserted Card state change: reset de-asserted ATR: 3b 9f 96 80 3f 87 00 80 31 e0 73 fe 21 1b 57 45 4d 75 30 30 17 51 bb PPS: ff 10 96 79 PPS: ff 10 96 79 Fi/Di switched to 512/32 TPDU: 00 a4 00 04 02 3f 00 61 2b ```
Any ideas what could be causing this? As I understand it, the Red with a HL7800 is basically just a bit pipe - i.e. no fancy applications - and I have checked and things like power management (CPSMS) are disabled.
I have asked in another thread about firmware versions and I did notice that Legato RTOS and "Apps" are mentioned by ATI9, so I am wondering if there is a "fancy application" that is interfering here.
``` ati9 HL7800.4.6.9 HL78xx.4.6.9.4.RK_02_01_02_00_137.20210615 2021/06/15 21:02:09 IMEI-SV: 3546160901940314 Legato RTOS: 18.09.6.ALT1250.rc8 2021/05/18 20:22:09 atSwi: 44.01 UBOOT: 01.03 Apps: RKAPP_02_01_02_00_120__c2a0a2a6e5dd44ea4710b32fe98e69dc72bab7ce MAC: ALT1250_02_01_02_00_123_FW PHY: 12.50.265649 PMP: 277291 SBUB: 0 SBFW: 0 RPuK: FPuK: RBUB: 0 RBFW: 0
OK ```
